flowchart LR

  subgraph INTENT["1. Path objective"]
    G1["Turn all prior closed platform truth into one explicit final judgment of the whole platform"]
    G2["Keep this path narrower than general platform completion and narrower than teardown and idle-safe closure"]
    G3["Answer how the platform turns blocker-free evidence from all required lanes into one final verdict object"]
  end

  subgraph ENTRY["2. Entry basis"]
    E1["The entry is not simply that many things are green"]
    E2["The entry is that all prior required phases have no unresolved blockers, and the source material needed to judge the whole platform is available"]
    E3["This path is not allowed to invent verdict from partial evidence"]
    E4["The final-phase closure sequence requires authority and handle closure first, full source matrix closure next, six-proof matrix closure after that, and only then final verdict publication"]
  end

  subgraph SPINE["5. Broad route logic"]
    R1["Authoritative source summaries"]
    R2["Full source matrix"]
    R3["Six-proof completeness matrix"]
    R4["Deterministic verdict assembly"]
    R5["Published full-verdict bundle at the run-scoped truth surface"]
  end

  subgraph CARRIES["4. What the path carries"]
    C1["Full source matrix across earlier closures"]
    C2["Six-proof matrix for each required major lane"]
    C3["Closure summaries from the earlier lanes"]
    C4["The verdict bundle itself"]
    C5["The readback identity needed to prove what was published is the same object that was generated"]
    C6["The managed implementation resolves scope-complete coverage from the authoritative source-matrix snapshot, appends summary checks from earlier final-phase steps, publishes the final-verdict bundle to run-control and the rendered run-scoped full-verdict path, and then verifies readback contains the same execution identity"]
  end

  subgraph LOGIC["6. Logical design reading"]
    L1["The platform treats platform activity, platform closure, and platform judgment as three different truths"]
    L2["The system is not saying because the earlier lanes closed green, the final verdict is obvious"]
    L3["It is saying there is a dedicated boundary where the platform must prove every required source is represented, every required proof class is complete, and the final judgment is then published deterministically"]
    L4["That is exactly the kind of systems-design maturity that helps the meta-goal, because it shows whole-platform claims are not left implicit or rhetorical"]
    L5["This is strong A-level design signal because whole-platform judgment has its own explicit closure object"]
  end

  subgraph SEATING["7. Concrete seating in the current wired system"]
    S1["This path is materially seated in the current wired platform"]
    S2["At the authority level, the run-close and final-phase contracts assign this boundary to the verdict-aggregator corridor and give it the full-platform closure anchor"]
    S3["At the execution level, the final-phase plan makes final verdict publication its own managed subphase"]
    S4["The implementation notes show that this lane was actually materialized and executed: it added a managed final-verdict closure mode, built the final-verdict bundle, published it to both run-control and the rendered full-verdict path, and verified readback identity via execution id"]
    S5["So the boundary is not just conceptual; it already exists as a real operated lane in the current platform"]
  end

  subgraph RATIONALE["8. Why the design looks like this"]
    Y1["The platform refuses two weak shortcuts: all upstream phases are green as proxy for valid whole-platform verdict, and a summary report as substitute for deterministic, scope-complete, proof-complete verdict object"]
    Y2["That is why the run-close and verdict contracts hard-pin the three-part pass condition: full source matrix blocker-free, six-proof matrix complete, and final verdict published"]
    Y3["The implementation trail reinforces the same intent"]
    Y4["When the verdict lane encountered legacy-scoped row handling, the correction was to keep the verdict boundary strict while making the source-scope rule explicit"]
    Y5["That is exactly what a serious final-judgment boundary should do"]
  end

  subgraph CONTRACT["9. What larger contracts are shaping this path"]
    X1["The full-platform closure contract defines the immediate rule: full source matrix blocker-free, six-proof matrix complete, and final verdict published"]
    X2["The full-platform proof-matrix law defines what complete means: for each major lane, the platform must publish proof of deploy, monitor, failure drill, recovery, rollback, and cost-control; no lane may claim closure without that six-part proof set"]
    X3["The final-phase execution contract shapes the current wired realization: strict sequencing, fail-closed blocker family for verdict inconsistency or publication failure, final verdict readability at the run-scoped truth surface, and parity checks across the closure summaries"]
  end

  subgraph TRADEOFFS["10. Trade-offs and constraints"]
    T1["This path deliberately adds one more formal judgment boundary after all the other major platform work is already done"]
    T2["That costs one more source-matrix aggregation step, one more proof-matrix completeness step, one more publication and readback verification step, and another explicit fail-closed blocker family"]
    T3["But that cost buys the ability to answer not just what each lane claims, but whether all required lanes were represented, whether each lane really satisfied all six proof classes, whether the final verdict was internally consistent, and whether the published verdict object is actually the same one the lane generated"]
    T4["That is very strong systems-design move, because it turns full platform green from slogan into governed, verifiable object"]
  end

  subgraph NECESSITY["11. Necessity test"]
    N1["If this path is removed, the platform can still close the spine, close learning, promote a bundle, reconstruct the run, and maybe even produce later operations snapshots"]
    N2["But it loses a clean answer to whether the whole platform is actually blocker-free"]
    N3["It loses a clean answer to whether every required proof class is represented"]
    N4["It loses a clean answer to whether the final claim of closure is internally consistent"]
    N5["It loses a clean answer to whether there is a single authoritative final verdict object at all"]
    N6["That would weaken A immediately because the platform could have many closure receipts but no explicit owner for whole-platform judgment that ties them together"]
    N7["The run-close and verdict contracts reject exactly that looseness by making the full source matrix, six-proof matrix, and final verdict bundle mandatory"]
  end

  subgraph CLOSURE["3. Owned outcome and 12. What this path proves for A"]
    O1["Full source matrix is aggregated blocker-free"]
    O2["Six-proof completeness is proven for required lanes"]
    O3["One final verdict bundle is published, readable, and identity-stable"]
    O4["Owned outcome: published, readable, deterministic full-platform verdict bundle"]
    A1["Purpose claim:<br/>the platform has a distinct job for turning all prior closure evidence into one explicit full-platform judgment"]
    A2["Intentionality claim:<br/>source-matrix completeness, six-proof completeness, and deterministic verdict publication are designed closure objects, not afterthoughts"]
    A3["Materialization claim:<br/>this boundary is concretely seated in the managed verdict-aggregator lane, with a real final-verdict bundle and readback identity checks already implemented"]
    A4["Contract claim:<br/>this path is governed by full source-matrix completeness, six-proof completeness across major lanes, deterministic verdict publication, readback identity, and fail-closed verdict inconsistency handling"]
    A5["Constraint-awareness claim:<br/>the platform already knows many green lanes do not automatically produce a trustworthy whole-platform claim, which is why the verdict boundary stays strict on scope, proof completeness, and publication identity"]
    A6["A-level meaning:<br/>the platform can issue a governed whole-platform judgment as a deterministic object rather than leaving final closure as an implicit interpretation of many smaller receipts"]
  end

